9:21 AM Prosecuting attorney Rick C Spoentgen in court for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant Samantha J. Williams in court.  Court states case and appearances.  DE does qualify for PD but just wanted to take the deal offered by the State.  Court advises DE of her right to counsel.  DE wishes to proceed w/o counsel.  Court advises her to get a plea/sent date from Br 3.  Court accepts waiver of time limits for prelim.  State asks that the DE confirm her address and then the DA's office will reach out to Br 3 to get a plea/sent date.   DE states address is correct but she's staying in Wisconsin until the matter is resolved.  DE states she will be calling the PD's office.  DE provided paperwork re: the PD's office.  State recommends that this be set for status hearing during the Br 3 intake.  Court goes off the record to address scheduling.  Back on the record, the Court makes a record that the parties  will get a new court date from Br 3 so DE can have a NOH in hand today.
